Sharks Send Dany Heatley to Wild for Martin Havlat in NHL Swap

-- B y   E r i k   M a t u s z e w s k i
-- 
2011-07-04T05:00:29Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-07-04/sharks-send-dany-heatley-to-wild-for-martin-havlat-in-nhl-swap.html
The San Jose Sharks traded Dany Heatley, who leads the  National Hockey League  with 58 game-
winning goals since entering the league in 2001, to the
 Minnesota Wild  for Martin Havlat in a swap of right wingers.  Heatley, 30, recorded 26 goals and 38 assists in 80 games
for the Sharks last season. The second overall pick in the 2000
NHL draft, Heatley has 325 goals and 364 assists in 669 career
games over nine seasons.  Havlat, also 30, had 22 goals and 40 assists for the Wild
last season. The 26th pick in the 1999 draft, he has 209 goals
and 303 assists in 621 games over 10 NHL seasons.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Erik Matuszewski in New York at 
 matuszewski@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Michael Sillup at   msillup@bloomberg.net  